as transformed the Display Window underneath the arcades into a staffage, a „folly garden.“ She is thus taking up the history of the Hofgarten, referencing&nbsp; the winter garden of King Ludwig II that was located in the first floor of the Hofgarten residence.<br></p>\n      </div><div style=\"position: absolute; top: 542px; left: 296.867px; width: 808px; height: 1181px;\"><ul class=\"imagegallery\"><li><a href=\"/images/545.jpeg\">© Heike Jobst</a></li></ul></div><div style=\"position: absolute; top: 1918px; left: 296.867px; width: 470px; height: 428px;\">\n      <p><em>Da drunten im Garten</em></p>\n<p><em>da ist ein schönes Paradies</em></p>\n<p><em>das ist so schön anzusehn</em></p>\n<p><em>daß man möchte drinne gehen</em></p>\n<p><em>daß man möchte drinne ja drinne gehen</em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em>Ich nehm es das Blümelein fein</em></p>\n<p><em>schließ es in Kämmerlein ein</em></p>\n<p><em>und stelz an ein einigen Ort</em></p>\n<p><em>daß es ja nicht verdorrt</em></p>\n<p><em>dass es ja nicht ja nicht verdorrt</em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>from: Des Knaben Wunderhorn (1808), Deutscher Liederhort (1856)</p>\n      </div></div>','1970-01-01','1970-01-01',1,1,1,0,NULL,NULL,'','JAHRESGABEN 2012',2012,10);
INSERT INTO `pages` VALUES (76,'ayzit-bostan','ayzit-bostan','The Local Contemporary: Ayzit Bostan','The Local Contemporary: Ayzit Bostan','','',56,57,'[[0,{\"type\":\"basetext\"},0,0],[0,{\"type\":\"imagegallery\",\"id\":373},{\"type\":\"textelement\",\"id\":292},0],[0,0,{\"type\":\"imagegallery\",\"id\":295},0],[0,0,0,0]]','<div style=\"position: absolute; top: 0px; left: 0px; width: 1835px; height: 2337px;\" id=\"container\"><div style=\"position: absolute; top: 91px; left: 296.867px; width: 470px; height: 38px;\">\n            <h1 class=\"basetext\"><img src=\"/hlimages/56.png\" alt=\"The Local Contemporary: Ayzit Bostan\"></h1>\n            <div>\n      \n          </div>\n  \n</div><div style=\"position: absolute; top: 310px; left: 296.867px; width: 453px; height: 679px;\"><ul class=\"imagegallery\"><li><a href=\"/images/586.jpeg\">Foto © U.Gebert</a></li><li><a href=\"/images/585.jpeg\">Foto © U.Gebert</a></li></ul></div><div style=\"position: absolute; top: 324px; left: 947.867px; width: 470px; height: 320px;\">\n      <p><span class=\"times-regular-center\">Ayzit Bostan</span><br><span class=\"times-regular-center\">14. Juli – 09. September 2012</span><br><br>Die Münchner Modedesignerin Ayzit Bostan (*1968 in Ankara, Türkei) arbeitet an der Schnittstelle von Design und Kunst. Neben ihren kommerziellen Kollektionen zeigt sie daher auch immer wieder Arbeiten in Kunst- und Ausstellungskontexten.  INSERT INTO `pages` VALUES (77,'john-giorno','john-giorno','No Country for Odd Poets: John Giorno','No Country for Odd Poets: John Giorno','','',50,51,'[[{\"type\":\"basetext\"},{\"type\":\"imagegallery\",\"id\":289},0],[{\"type\":\"imagegallery\",\"id\":288},{\"type\":\"textelement\",\"id\":286},0],[{\"type\":\"vimeovideo\",\"id\":368},{\"type\":\"imagegallery\",\"id\":287},0]]','<div style=\"position: absolute; top: 0px; left: 0px; width: 2420px; height: 2511px;\" id=\"container\"><div style=\"position: absolute; top: 91px; left: 318.5px; width: 470px; height: 281px;\">\n            <h1 class=\"basetext\"><img src=\"/hlimages/50.png\" alt=\"No Country for Odd Poets: John Giorno\"></h1>\n            <div>\n      \n          </div>\n  \n</div><div style=\"position: absolute; top: 91px; left: 1197px; width: 927px; height: 618px;\"><ul class=\"imagegallery\"><li><a href=\"/images/528.jpeg\">No Country For Odd Poets: John Giorno. Foto © G. Blum</a></li><li><a href=\"/images/529.jpeg\">No Country For Odd Poets: John Giorno. Foto © G. Blum</a></li><li><a href=\"/images/530.jpeg\">No Country For Odd Poets: John Giorno. Foto © G. Blum</a></li><li><a href=\"/images/532.jpeg\">No Country For Odd Poets: John Giorno. Foto © G. Blum</a></li><li><a href=\"/images/531.jpeg\">No Country For Odd Poets: John Giorno. Foto © G. Blum</a></li><li><a href=\"/images/533.jpeg\">No Country For Odd Poets: John Giorno. Foto © G. Blum</a></li></ul></div><div style=\"position: absolute; top: 890px; left: 91px; width: 925px; height: 617px;\"><ul class=\"imagegallery\"><li><a href=\"/images/512.jpeg\">No Country For Odd Poets: John Giorno. Foto © G. Blum</a></li><li><a href=\"/images/513.jpeg\">No Country For Odd Poets: John Giorno. Foto © G. Blum</a></li></ul></div><div style=\"position: absolute; top: 890px; left: 1197px; width: 470px; height: 674px;\">\n      <h2 class=\"courier-regular\"><strong>JOHN GIORNO<span class=\"times-regular-center\"><br>Lesung und Performance am 22. Mai 2012, 19 Uhr</span></strong><br><br>John Giorno (*1936, New York) ist eine der Schlüsselfiguren der New Yorker Beat Generation und der Begründer der Performance Poetry. Dichter, bildender Künstler und ein Performer der Extraklasse. 1965 gründete der Weggefährte von Künstlerkollegen wie Andy Warhol, Robert Rauschenberg, William Burroughs, Laurie Anderson und Keith Haring das Label \"Giorno Poetry Systems\", das den innovativen Gebrauch von neuen Technologien in den Vordergrund stellte. Das Label veröffentlichte LPs und CDs, Videos und Filme von Autoren, die mit Musik und/oder Performance arbeiten. <br>John Giorno wurde 1963/64 durch den Experimentalfilm \"Sleep\" von Andy Warhol bekannt, in dem Giorno sechs Stunden schlafend zu sehen ist. Warhol übte einen wichtigen Einfluss auf Giornos künstlerische Entwicklung aus und ermunterte ihn schließlich mit Poesie, Performance und Tonbandgeräten zu experimentieren. Giorno ist ein Veteran des Genres \"Spoken Word\". Eine von Giornos legendärsten Aktionen ist DIAL-A-POEM (1968), ein Experiment zur Untersuchung der Massenkommunikation, bei dem täglich wechselnde Gedichte (700 von 55 Dichtern) auf Anrufbeantwortern abgefragt werden konnten. <br>John Giorno freut sich, zum ersten Mal seit sechzig Jahren wieder Gelegenheit zum Reiten zu bekommen, und bekundet hinterher, dass das Gefühl dasselbe geblieben sei.</h2>\n<p class=\"courier-regular\"><br>Für den musikalischen Rahmen sorgen DJ Gebrüder (Afrodermitis &amp; Peter Friedrich)</p>\n      </div><div style=\"position: absolute; top: 1759px; left: 91px; width: 600px; height: 375px;\">\n  <object height=\"375\" width=\"600\">\n    <param name=\"allowfullscreen\" value=\"true\">\n    <param name=\"allowscriptaccess\" value=\"always\">\n    <param name=\"movie\" value=\"http://vimeo.com/moogaloop.swf?clip_id=47655418&amp;server=vimeo.com&amp;show_title=0&amp;show_byline=0&amp;show_portrait=0&amp;color=ffffff&amp;fullscreen=1&amp;autoplay=0&amp;loop=0\">\n    <embed src=\"http://vimeo.com/moogaloop.swf?clip_id=47655418&amp;server=vimeo.com&amp;show_title=0&amp;show_byline=0&amp;show_portrait=0&amp;color=ffffff&amp;fullscreen=1&amp;autoplay=0&amp;loop=0\" type=\"application/x-shockwave-flash\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" allowscriptaccess=\"always\" height=\"375\" width=\"600\">\n  </object>\n</div><div style=\"position: absolute; top: 1759px; left: 1197px; width: 470px; height: 662px;\"><ul class=\"imagegallery\"><li><a href=\"/images/511.png\">Bild</a></li><li><a href=\"/images/510.png\">Bild</a></li></ul></div></div>','<div style=\"position: absolute; top: 0px; left: 0px; width: 2420px; height: 2443px;\" id=\"container\"><div style=\"position: absolute; top: 91px; left: 318.5px; width: 470px; height: 281px;\">\n            <h1 class=\"basetext\"><img src=\"/hlimages/51.png\" alt=\"No Country for Odd Poets: John Giorno\"></h1>\n            <div>\n      \n          </div>\n  \n</div><div style=\"position: absolute; top: 91px; left: 1197px; width: 927px; height: 618px;\"><ul class=\"imagegallery\"><li><a href=\"/images/528.jpeg\">No Country For Odd Poets: John Giorno. Photo © G. Blum</a></li><li><a href=\"/images/529.jpeg\">No Country For Odd Poets: John Giorno. Photo © G. Blum</a></li><li><a href=\"/images/530.jpeg\">No Country For Odd Poets: John Giorno. Photo © G. Blum</a></li><li><a href=\"/images/532.jpeg\">No Country For Odd Poets: John Giorno. Photo © G. Blum</a></li><li><a href=\"/images/531.jpeg\">No Country For Odd Poets: John Giorno. Photo © G. Blum</a></li><li><a href=\"/images/533.jpeg\">No Country For Odd Poets: John Giorno. Photo © G. Blum</a></li></ul></div><div style=\"position: absolute; top: 890px; left: 91px; width: 925px; height: 617px;\"><ul class=\"imagegallery\"><li><a href=\"/images/512.jpeg\">No Country For Odd Poets: John Giorno. Photo © G. Blum</a></li><li><a href=\"/images/513.jpeg\">No Country For Odd Poets: John Giorno. Photo © G. Blum</a></li></ul></div><div style=\"position: absolute; top: 890px; left: 1197px; width: 470px; height: 620px;\">\n      <h2 class=\"courier-regular\"><strong>JOHN GIORNO</strong><br><strong><span class=\"times-regular-center\">reading and performance on 22 May, 2012, 7 pm</span></strong><br><br>John Giorno (*1936, New York City) is one of the key figures of the Beat Generation the founder of Performance Poetry. He is a poet, artist and exceptional performer, whose friends and colleagues include Andy Warhol, Robert Rauschenberg, William Burroughs, Laurie Anderson und Keith Haring. In 1965 he founded the music label \'John Giorno Poetry Systems\', whose emphasis was on innovative use of new technologies. The label released lps, cds, videos and films of authors who were working with music and/or performance.<br>John Giorno\'s claim to fame was the experimental film \'Sleep\' by Andy Warhol in 1963/64, in which Giorno can be seen sleeping for 6 hours. Warhol had a big influence on Giorno\'s artistic development and encouraged him to experiment with poetry, performance and tape-recorders. Giorno is a veteran of the \'Spoken Word\' genre. One of Giorno\'s most legendary actions is DIAL-A-POEM (1968), which was an experiment analysing mass communication, where one was able to call up the number and listen to daily-changing poems (700 by 55 poets) recorded on answering machines.</h2>\n<h2 class=\"courier-regular\"><br>The evening is musically accompanied (prior- and post-reading) by DJ Gebrüder (Afrodermitis &amp; Peter Friedrich)<br><br><br></h2>\n      </div><div style=\"position: absolute; top: 1691px; left: 91px; width: 600px; height: 375px;\">\n  <object height=\"375\" width=\"600\">\n    <param name=\"allowfullscreen\" value=\"true\">\n    <param name=\"allowscriptaccess\" value=\"always\">\n    <param name=\"movie\" value=\"http://vimeo.com/moogaloop.swf?clip_id=47655418&amp;server=vimeo.com&amp;show_title=0&amp;show_byline=0&amp;show_portrait=0&amp;color=ffffff&amp;fullscreen=1&amp;autoplay=0&amp;loop=0\">\n    <embed src=\"http://vimeo.com/moogaloop.swf?clip_id=47655418&amp;server=vimeo.com&amp;show_title=0&amp;show_byline=0&amp;show_portrait=0&amp;color=ffffff&amp;fullscreen=1&amp;autoplay=0&amp;loop=0\" type=\"application/x-shockwave-flash\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" allowscriptaccess=\"always\" height=\"375\" width=\"600\">\n  </object>\n</div><div style=\"position: absolute; top: 1691px; left: 1197px; width: 470px; height: 662px;\"><ul class=\"imagegallery\"><li><a href=\"/images/511.png\">Image</a></li><li><a href=\"/images/510.png\">Image</a></li></ul></div></div>','<div style=\"position: absolute; top: 0px; left: 0px